dismissalText.commentary: Elton Chigumbura c Chanderpaul b Sammy 42 (78b 2x4 3x6 84m) SR: 53.84

dismissalComment.html: goes for that pull shot again, connects but doesn't clear the deep backward square-leg fielder. Sammy celebrates by pumping his fist .. Good rear-guard action from Chigumbura ends

dismissalText.commentary: Graeme Cremer c Miller b Bravo 15 (41b 0x4 0x6 48m) SR: 36.58

dismissalComment.html: moves outside leg stump, was thinking about the big hit over the off-side field but ended up shoveling the length delivery to cover. It lobs up for a simple catch.

headshotImage.longCaption: Timycen Maruma player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Wicket first ball for Bravo. It landed on a length around off stump and Maruma leaned forward to defend. and the ball bounces rather late and bounds off the handle towards gully. Sammy dives forward to take a good catch

Matsikenyeri's misery ends. He never looked in and he is out now. Full delivery on the off stump line, straightening a bit and Matsikenyeri did many things wrong - he was late in getting forward, he stumbled out instead of taking a fluent step, he pushed out blindly, he assumed the ball would come in and lost his off stump.

image.caption: Tatenda Taibu
image.longCaption: Tatenda Taibu portrait, World Cup 2011, February 11, 2011

dismissalComment.html: Another short delivery outside off stump, Taibu plays the upper cut but hits it straight to third man. Zimbabwe are really tottering again. What a royal mess they find themselves in.
moves outside leg stump, was thinking about the big hit over the off-side field but ended up shoveling the length delivery to cover. It lobs up for a simple catch.

dismissalComment.html: Rampaul takes out Masakadza. Big early blow this. What a cracker of a delivery. It landed short of length and suddenly reared up sharply chest-high of the startled and out of position Masakadza who just stabbed it behind.

Clatter..........The off stump has gone for a nice little walk. It was full, it started from outside off and moved in late. Brendon Taylor is very late in getting forward and leaves a big gaping hole between bat and pad. mistake! Timber!

dismissalText.commentary: Vusi Sibanda run out (Pollard) 11 (23b 1x4 0x6 59m) SR: 47.82

dismissalComment.html: Sibanda is run out It was pushed to the off side ... Sibanda sets off for a run before stopping. Too late as Taibu keeps rushing on. Sibanda just stood there as Pollard swoops on the ball. Both batsmen are almost the striker's end. Easy run out . Pollard runs to the non-striker's end to take off the bails.

commentTextItems.html: spins down the leg side , and wide .. that's it West Indies have won the series

commentPostTextItems.html: Zimbabwe were restricted for a low total. The chase should have been easy but it wasn't. West Indies struggled against spin - Cremer, the leggie, was really good - but managed to hold out in the end to clinch the series.
That's it from us. Thanks for logging on. Good bye and good luck.

dismissalText.commentary: Hamilton Masakadza c †Ramdin b Rampaul 0 (9b 0x4 0x6 5m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: Rampaul takes out Masakadza. Big early blow this. What a cracker of a delivery. It landed short of length and suddenly reared up sharply chest-high of the startled and out of position Masakadza who just stabbed it behind.

headshotImage.longCaption: Dwayne Bravo player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Timycen Maruma c Sammy b Bravo 9 (21b 1x4 0x6 25m) SR: 42.85

dismissalComment.html: Wicket first ball for Bravo. It landed on a length around off stump and Maruma leaned forward to defend. and the ball bounces rather late and bounds off the handle towards gully. Sammy dives forward to take a good catch

headshotImage.caption: Ravi Rampaul player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ravi Rampaul player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Brendan Taylor b Rampaul 1 (6b 0x4 0x6 4m) SR: 16.66

dismissalComment.html: Clatter..........The off stump has gone for a nice little walk. It was full, it started from outside off and moved in late. Brendon Taylor is very late in getting forward and leaves a big gaping hole between bat and pad. mistake! Timber!

headshotImage.caption: Kieron Pollard player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Kieron Pollard player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Vusi Sibanda run out (Pollard) 11 (23b 1x4 0x6 59m) SR: 47.82

dismissalComment.html: Sibanda is run out It was pushed to the off side ... Sibanda sets off for a run before stopping. Too late as Taibu keeps rushing on. Sibanda just stood there as Pollard swoops on the ball. Both batsmen are almost the striker's end. Easy run out . Pollard runs to the non-striker's end to take off the bails.

headshotImage.caption: Dwayne Bravo player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dwayne Bravo player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Stuart Matsikenyeri b Bravo 1 (9b 0x4 0x6 9m) SR: 11.11

dismissalComment.html: Matsikenyeri's misery ends. He never looked in and he is out now. Full delivery on the off stump line, straightening a bit and Matsikenyeri did many things wrong - he was late in getting forward, he stumbled out instead of taking a fluent step, he pushed out blindly, he assumed the ball would come in and lost his off stump.

dismissalText.commentary: Tatenda Taibu c Miller b Bravo 14 (33b 0x4 0x6 45m) SR: 42.42

dismissalComment.html: Another short delivery outside off stump, Taibu plays the upper cut but hits it straight to third man. Zimbabwe are really tottering again. What a royal mess they find themselves in.

dismissalText.commentary: Greg Lamb c & b Miller 12 (50b 0x4 0x6 53m) SR: 24

dismissalComment.html: After two quick deliveries, Miller slows up the pace,and Lamb pushes  out early and checks his shot and the ball lobs to the right of non-striker and Miller gets across in time with a lunging dive to take the catch

headshotImage.longCaption: Shivnarine Chanderpaul player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Elton Chigumbura c Chanderpaul b Sammy 42 (78b 2x4 3x6 84m) SR: 53.84

dismissalComment.html: goes for that pull shot again, connects but doesn't clear the deep backward square-leg fielder. Sammy celebrates by pumping his fist .. Good rear-guard action from Chigumbura ends

headshotImage.caption: Dwayne Bravo player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dwayne Bravo player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Graeme Cremer c Miller b Bravo 15 (41b 0x4 0x6 48m) SR: 36.58

dismissalComment.html: moves outside leg stump, was thinking about the big hit over the off-side field but ended up shoveling the length delivery to cover. It lobs up for a simple catch.

dismissalText.commentary: Shivnarine Chanderpaul c Price b Chigumbura 2 (12b 0x4 0x6 7m) SR: 16.66

dismissalComment.html: Chanderpaul is out. Short in length outside off, Chanderpaul tries to pull it from there but top edges it to mid-on where Price holds the catch

dismissalText.commentary: Denesh Ramdin lbw b Cremer 12 (26b 1x4 0x6 44m) SR: 46.15

dismissalComment.html: Trapped in front. West Indies continue to be clueless against spin. It landed on a length on middle stump line and just about straightened to hit him right in front. Ramdin was pushing his bat well outside the line. Cremer has really impressed in this series. Very good leggie.

dismissalText.commentary: Dwayne Bravo c Masakadza b Cremer 6 (8b 1x4 0x6 6m) SR: 75

dismissalComment.html: Bravo combusts! It was a flighted delivery around off stump and Bravo goes for an expansive inside-out drive and edges it straight to slip! Good bowling but what a self-destructive streak that was.
